Quote:  I was left at Tarndale to keep an eye on a lot of young cattle we had put above a bull break in the Wairau. I was guided by fences out to the Wairau River from where the bull break was easy to locate. 1996. ibid. 92 We then mustered the head of Rainbow back-boxing the two mobs and putting them above the bull break before riding to Tarndale.
